Experiment No: 1

Aim:
To write a C program that calculates the electricity bill for a consumer based on the number of units consumed.

Algorithm:
Start
Input consumer name, consumer number, and number of units consumed.
Compute the charge per unit according to this rule (example):
0–100 units → ₹1.50 per unit
101–200 units → ₹2.50 per unit
201–500 units → ₹4.00 per unit
Above 500 units → ₹6.00 per unit
Calculate total bill = units × rate
If total bill > ₹1000, add 10% surcharge.
Display all details: name, number, units, and final amount.
End

 Program :
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int consumer_no;
    char name[50];
    float units, charge_per_unit, total, surcharge, net_amount;

    // Input
    printf("Enter Consumer Number: ");
    scanf("%d", &consumer_no);
    printf("Enter Consumer Name: ");
    scanf("%s", name);
    printf("Enter Units Consumed: ");
    scanf("%f", &units);

    // Calculate charge per unit
    if (units <= 100)
        charge_per_unit = 1.50;
    else if (units <= 200)
        charge_per_unit = 2.50;
    else if (units <= 500)
        charge_per_unit = 4.00;
    else
        charge_per_unit = 6.00;

    total = units * charge_per_unit;

    // Add surcharge if needed
    if (total > 1000)
        surcharge = total * 0.10;
    else
        surcharge = 0;

    net_amount = total + surcharge;

    // Output
    printf("\n--- Electricity Bill ---\n");
    printf("Consumer No.   : %d\n", consumer_no);
    printf("Consumer Name  : %s\n", name);
    printf("Units Consumed : %.2f\n", units);
    printf("Charge/Unit    : ₹%.2f\n", charge_per_unit);
    printf("Total Amount   : ₹%.2f\n", total);
    printf("Surcharge      : ₹%.2f\n", surcharge);
    printf("Net Amount     : ₹%.2f\n", net_amount);

    return 0;
}

Input:
Enter Consumer Number: 1023
Enter Consumer Name: Ramesh
Enter Units Consumed: 250

Output:
Consumer No.   : 1023
Consumer Name  : Ramesh
Units Consumed : 250.00
Charge/Unit    : ₹4.00
Total Amount   : ₹1000.00
Surcharge      : ₹0.00
Net Amount     : ₹1000.00

Result:
The program successfully calculates and displays the electricity bill for a consumer based on the units
